{
  "text": "The Norwegian conventional health care system can be perceived as a context of patients' use of traditional healing as well as their use of CAM, as the participants in this study who relate to traditional healers at the same time also receive treatment within the conventional health care system and thus relate to biomedical knowledge [CITATION_1] Salamonsen, 2013) . The content and meaning of this combined use of non-conventional and conventional health practices is an interesting and so far under-explored issue of contemporary health practices.",
  "citation_candidates": [
